The paper discusses extensions of first-order logic that are relevant to several subfields of computer science. The use of fixed point operators is particularly relevant to logic (cs.LO) and database theory (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of iteration operators, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of temporal logic formulae, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS).
